The paper deals with image colorization, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning networks for colorization is also a key aspect of the paper, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.MM) category. The paper also involves graphics (cs.GR) as it deals with manga images, which are a form of graphic art. The use of adversarial loss and the semi-automatic nature of the colorization process could also place the paper in the category of generative models (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
